  <guide>
    <section section_id="general_guide" title="General Guide">
      <p>• Play Trial Battle ([Lv4](image:catalog/shared/summon_event/Trial_Lvl_4.png|preview)).</p>
      <p>• Complete All Tasks.</p>
      <p>• Use Tickets to gain Event Currency.</p>
      <p>• Spend Event Currency in the Event Shop.</p>
      <p>• Spend {item:aeon_core}s on [Legendary Characters](#faq-legendary_character_choice).</p>
    </section>
    <section section_id="shop_economy" title="Shop Economy">
      <p>Keys: Generally most efficient and therefore recommended.</p>
      <p>Here are some other options.</p>
      <p>Legendary Artifact: If you can complete an artifact set. [explained here](#faq-legendary_artifact)</p>
      <p>Discounted S-Tier Gear: It changes between events. If you use them, you might want to get them.</p>
      <p>Character Shards: Not efficient, but if you can unlock or star-up a character, it's not a completely bad option.</p>
    </section>
  </guide>

  <faq>
    <item faq_id="aeon_core_intro" question="What are {item:aeon_core|nolink}s?">
      <answer>
        <p>{item:aeon_core|nolink}s are an extremely rare Summon Event currency gained through luck or [pity](#faq-aeon_core_odds) when using Tickets.</p>
        <p>They are used in the event shop to buy Legendary Characters and Artifacts.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="aeon_core_odds" question="What are the odds of getting an {item:aeon_core} before pity?">
      <answer>
        <p>Assuming a 0.12% chance per pull and pity at 400 pulls, the average is about 317.8 pulls.</p>
        <p>Before pity, the cumulative odds are roughly:</p>
        <p>• 25% at 240 pulls.</p>
        <p>• 50% at 577 pulls.</p>
        <p>• 90% at 1,918 pulls.</p>
        <p>• 99% at 3,835 pulls.</p>
        <p>Since pity guarantees an {item:aeon_core} by 400 pulls, anything above 38% happens after pity, not before it.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="ticket_total_per_event" question="How many Tickets can you get per event?">
      <answer>
        <p>You can get up to 55 from tasks and the free fund, meaning it can take up to 8 events to get an {item:aeon_core} if you are unlucky.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="buy_tickets_with_gems" question="Can I buy tickets with gems?">
      <answer>
        <p>No, you cannot buy tickets with any in-game currencies.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="best_spend_money" question="What should I buy with money to speed up my progress?">
      <answer>
        <p>The Fund is the best value per ticket (50 tickets), followed by the daily packs.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="faq_pack_value" question="What packs give the most value?">
      <answer>
        <p>The Fund is considered the best value per ticket.</p>
        <p>![Summon event pack value comparison](catalog/shared/summon_event/Prices.png "Pack value comparison for Summon Event.")</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="progress_carry_over" question="Does progress save between events?">
      <answer>
        <p>Only your luck/pity carries over to the next event. Make sure to spend your tickets and currency before the event ends.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="legendary_character_choice" question="What Legendary Character should I buy?">
      <answer>
        <p>It depends on your needs and preferences, but generally:</p>
        <p>• For PvE, Thor is considered the best and most game changing for most players.</p>
        <p>• For PvP, Cleo is generally considered best for her damage output.</p>
        <p>• For PvP, Atreus is the tankier option, but usually considered the worst of the three if you do not already own the others.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="legendary_artifact" question="When is a Legendary Artifact worth it?">
      <answer>
        <p>If you can complete an artifact set, it is generally worth it.</p>
        <p>For example, purchasing the feather would activate the set bonus, resulting in a 4% increase to Attack Power and Max Health.</p>
        <image
          src="catalog/shared/misc/media/legendary_artifact_example.png"
          alt="Artifact set bonus example showing +4% ATK PWR and +4% Max HP"
          caption="Completing a set activates the bonus."
        />
      </answer>
    </item>
